          Esc

               This allows you to either execute an external shell program
               such as Craft or Gulam, or to execute a program directly from
               within BinkleyTerm.  Pressing <Esc> causes a box to pop up.
               If you press return then a shell program is executed as
               specified by the SHELL or COMSPEC environment variables
               (exactly the same as if you had pressed Alt-J).  If you type
               in a complete program path and filename then that program is
               executed.  If you have a resident shell such as Craft
               installed, then whatever you type is passed to the shell
               for execution.

          Space

               This key may be used to abort polls and to unblank the screen
               (when the 'ScreenBlank' option is used).  This key is ignored
               when pressed during BinkleyTerm idle time (waiting for calls).

          Home

               Resort the outbound window.

          Ctrl-C or Ctrl-F

               Allows the flavour of mail to be changed.  Pressing this
               causes a pop-up box to appear, where you may specify an
               address and the flavour of mail to convert from and to.  The
               flavours are:
                 N : Normal
                 C : Crash
                 H : Hold
                 D : Direct
               See section 3.3 of the User's guide for more details about
               mail flavours.

          $

               Kills all the bad connect status files (These are found in the
               Outbound folders with names like '*.$$?').

















